dolore. Singleton: "Strictly speaking, the soul, without the body, may
not be said to be circumscribed by space; but the soul, in this case, is
going to take on at least the semblance of a body, and the locating of it
in space anticipates the fact. Compare Thomas Aquinas, ^Summa theol~. I,
q. 52, a. 2: 'Sic igitur patet quod diversimode esse in loco convenit
